WHAT THIS FILE COVERS
==========================================================================

This repository contains two categories of intellectual property,
each under a different licensing regime. Read both sections.

==========================================================================
SECTION A — ROYALTY-FREE: THE CARD PROTOCOL
==========================================================================

The following elements define the CARD open protocol and are licensed
on a Royalty-Free (RF) basis consistent with the W3C Patent Policy:

  - The CARD data model: Entity CARDs, Data CARDs, and Use CARDs
  - The JSON Schema (card-v0.1.json)
  - The SQL migrations (001–006) as a reference implementation
  - The Verification Endpoint interface contract (request/response format)
  - The demo seed script (bob-bethany-demo-seed.sql)
  - All documentation in this repository (README, docs/)

WHAT YOU CAN DO (RF elements):
  ✓ Implement the CARD data model in any language or storage engine
  ✓ Build applications that create, read, and manage CARDs
  ✓ Build clients that call a Verification Endpoint
  ✓ Use, modify, and redistribute the reference SQL and JSON Schema
  ✓ Use these materials for commercial or non-commercial purposes
  ✓ Fork this repository and build on it

NO royalty, license fee, or permission is required for the above uses.
This commitment is irrevocable for any implementation that conforms to
the CARD protocol as defined in the published W3C Position Paper.

==========================================================================
SECTION B — PATENT-RESERVED: TRUST NETWORK OPERATION
==========================================================================

US Provisional Patent Application 63/992,579 describes a method for
operating a trust network that verifies CARD-based credentials. The
patent covers the OPERATIONAL METHOD, not the data model or protocol.

Specifically, the patent covers the integrated method by which a
network operator:
  - Authenticates requesting parties via API key infrastructure
  - Performs CARD verification with rate limiting and abuse controls
  - Maintains tamper-evident audit logs of all verification events
  - Operates a three-tier enforcement system (technical, contractual,
    and governance) as a unified trust network

WHAT THIS MEANS FOR YOU:

  If you are BUILDING WITH CARDs (implementing the data model, calling
  a Verification Endpoint, creating CARD-aware applications):
    → You are using Section A elements. No license required. Build freely.

  If you are OPERATING A TRUST NETWORK (running a verification service
  that authenticates callers, rate-limits requests, maintains audit logs,
  and enforces trust policies on behalf of multiple parties):
    → You may be practicing the method described in the patent.
    → Contact ip@opn.li to discuss licensing.

The distinction is between USING the protocol (free) and OPERATING
the network infrastructure (licensed).

